%N A051755 Consider problem of placing N queens on an n X n board so that each queen attacks precisely 2 others. Sequence gives maximal number of queens.
%C A051755 3 followed by the positive even integers starting with 4. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Feb 09 2014
%C A051755 Also, least crossing number of a prime knot with braid index n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Feb 14 2023
%C A051755 Proof: the crossing number of a knot with braid index n is at least 2n-2 for n>=3, by the Ohyama bound on the crossing number in terms of braid index. Also, for n>=1, the twist knot with 2n twists has the continued fraction [2,2n] - with [2,2] being the figure-eight knot. It has crossing number 2n+2 (as witnessed by its alternating knot diagram as closure of a rational tangle), while its braid index is n+2 (by Murasugi's braid index formula for 2-bridge links). See the answer and comment to the linked question at MathOverflow. - _Hermann Gruber_, Oct 13 2025
